<p>We use Font Awesome icons to accent elements on webpages and web applications. See below for examples and the list of approved icons.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>

<ul>
   <li>Use icons to accent exisiting elements</li>
   <li>Basic functionality CAN use only icons</li>
   <li>Complex interations should use text rather than icons</li>
</ul>

<p>You can use any of the approved icons with <code>&lt;i class="fa fa-icon-name" title="icon title"&gt;</i></code>. See the Font Awesome <a href="http://fontawesome.io/">website</a> for more ways to configure the icons.</p>

<p>In order to use Font Awesome you'll need to include a link to the CDN: <code>&lt;link href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-wvfXpqpZZVQGK6TAh5PVlGOfQNHSoD2xbE+QkPxCAFlNEevoEH3Sl0sibVcOQVnN" crossorigin="anonymous"&gt;</code></p>


